# .cursorrules — Topskilly Project
# Paste this file at the root of your project. Cursor reads it automatically.

You are building Topskilly — a global skills lead marketplace.

## Stack
Web: Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
Mobile: React Native + Expo SDK 51 + Expo Router + NativeWind
Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + RLS + Storage)
Payments: Razorpay (India) + Stripe (Global) + Apple IAP (iOS)
State: Zustand (mobile) + React Context (web)
Email: Resend
CDN/Security: Cloudflare
Hosting: Vercel (web) + EAS (mobile)

## Rules — Always Follow
- Always use TypeScript. Never use plain JavaScript.
- Always enable Row Level Security on every Supabase table.
- Never hardcode API keys. Use environment variables (.env.local).
- Every lead post MUST require phone OTP verification via Twilio/Supabase.
- The coin unlock transaction MUST be atomic (use a Supabase PostgreSQL function).
- Use server components by default in Next.js; use "use client" only when needed.
- Use Supabase SSR client (createServerClient) in Server Components and API routes.
- Use Supabase browser client (createBrowserClient) in Client Components.
- All API routes must validate the user session before processing.
- Max 3-5 professionals can unlock the same lead (check buyer_count before unlock).
- No refund logic needed — OTP at lead post guarantees authenticity.

## Brand
- Primary colour: #1A56DB (Topskilly Blue)
- Font: Inter
- Tone: Premium, trustworthy, fast

## File Structure
apps/web/          — Next.js 14 App Router web app
apps/mobile/       — React Native + Expo mobile app
packages/shared/   — Shared TypeScript types and utilities
supabase/          — Database schema, RLS policies, Edge Functions

## Database Tables
users, tutor_profiles, leads, lead_unlocks, purchases, wallets, messages, reviews, categories

## Coin Pricing
- 200 coins = 1 lead unlock
- Rs. 2,000/month subscription = 2,000 coins (20 leads)
- Coins never expire
